<br>
Most often you hope for the best but because there are multiple vendors in the mix things invariably get skewed, well ok screwed.  One vendor says his video card works w/another vendors software but only under DX8.01a circumstances.  Maybe the letter “a” got overlooked.  Multiply that by dozens of vendors and things do go south.<br>
<br>
The memory issues, well it is what it is.  I am a bit surprised that half a gig is needed, but that is becoming common now in the client/server commercial sector.  Me thinks this is a programming paradigm where brute force rather than articulate programming is the order.  Been that way since Pentium class processors came out.  IMO don’t look for it to stop.  <br>
<br>
In any event, barring DX8 issues, peeps ought to be able to run SoV without memory upgrades.  Well maybe not the peeps with 64 or 96MB but they gonna need to upgrade sometime for MS reasons.<br>
<br>
Sure the expansion looks like a rush job.  It prolly is.  Sure DAoC might have influenced but I am betting Verant has a fiscal / calendar year end and this project had to be launched to service and satisfy investment.<br>
<br>
Peeps are angry, change has that affect.<br>
<br>
Calm blue ocean, calm blue ocean, calm blue ocean {repeat}<br>
